DYN500
Styled as a virtual 500-Series format module, the DYN500 provides soft-knee compression coupled with gentle tape-saturation style overdrive if driven past 0dBFS.
 
Designed as a high quality 'one in every channel' compressor / dynamics plug-in for Digital Audio Workstations, the DYN500 can be used in mono or stereo channels and is economical with CPU resources while delivering professional console grade processing.

EQ500
Styled as a virtual 500-Series format module, the EQ500 provides adjustable high and low frequency shelves and a versatile mid-range parametric EQ.
 
Designed as a high quality 'one in every channel' EQ plug-in for Digital Audio Workstations, the EQ500 uses our Analogue Filter Modelling algorithms to accurately replicate a natural sounding analogue filter response without requiring high sample rates or CPU intensive upsampling, allowing more plugin instances in a typical DAW.

FC-70
First developed for linux audio workstations, the FC70 is now available as a Windows / Mac VST and Mac Audio Unit. The FC70 emulates the legendary smooth, effortless dynamic control and uniquely musical character of the classic Fairchild 670 limiter.
Modelled using measured data and schematics from genuine hardware, the FC70 uses a fully balanced design, combined with innovative delay-free feedback topology to emulate the original circuitry. The sidechain includes the fast attack and program dependent release settings of the original, combined with Lateral / Vertical, Independent and Linked stereo channel modes.

PTC-2A
First developed for linux audio workstations, the FC70 is now available as a Windows / Mac VST and Mac Audio Unit. The FC70 emulates the legendary smooth, effortless dynamic control and uniquely musical character of the classic Fairchild 670 limiter.
Modelled using measured data and schematics from genuine hardware, the FC70 uses a fully balanced design, combined with innovative delay-free feedback topology to emulate the original circuitry. The sidechain includes the fast attack and program dependent release settings of the original, combined with Lateral / Vertical, Independent and Linked stereo channel modes.

PTH-2A
Inspired by the Pultec EQH equalizers, the PTH-2A provides a cost-effective feature subset of the PTC-2A / EQP-1A emulation. The PTH-2A uses the same filter emulation technology, providing separately adjustable LF Boost and Attenuate controls for the signature Pultec low-end sound, with three selectable frequencies.
